From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: WarChaos Apple Silicon contributors
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] winemac.drv: Add relative mouse (raw input) mode for FPS
 pointer grabs

This ports the relative-pointer behavior from winewayland.drv (GitLab MR
!5869) to the macOS driver, fixing the ~2s mouselook latency that makes
FPS games unplayable under winemac.drv (e.g. WarChaos/CryEngine).

Root cause
----------
WineApplicationController -handleMouseMove: in cocoa_app.m only emits
MOUSE_MOVED_RELATIVE events when the cursor is "pinned" against the
clip/desktop boundary (the computedPoint-one-step-ahead heuristic).
In the interior of its range it emits MOUSE_MOVED_ABSOLUTE using
CGEventGetLocation. An FPS that calls ClipCursor + ShowCursor(FALSE) +
RegisterRawInputDevices keeps the cursor in the interior almost all the
time, so registered raw input devices never receive usable relative
deltas in WM_INPUT -> fast flicks are dropped / lagged.

This also explains why UseConfinementCursorClipping=N (the CGEventTap
clip handler) did not help: the event tap rewrites CGEventGetLocation to
the pinned synthesized location, so computedPoint stays in-bounds and
the heuristic still forces absolute.

The fix
-------
When the new opt-in registry key
    HKCU\Software\Wine\Mac Driver\RawInput = Y
is set, and the client has hidden the cursor and is clipping it (the
canonical FPS pointer-grab condition, matching winewayland.drv's
!is_visible && constraint_hwnd check), always take the relative branch
and feed the true per-event CGEvent deltas (kCGMouseEventDeltaX/Y, exposed
as NSEvent -deltaX/-deltaY). The existing macdrv_mouse_moved() handler
already forwards MOUSE_MOVED_RELATIVE as MOUSEEVENTF_MOVE (no
MOUSEEVENTF_ABSOLUTE) via NtUserSendHardwareInput, and win32u synthesizes
WM_INPUT for registered raw input devices (per the merged Bernon
patchset, 2019). No changes are needed in mouse.c.

No new RID infrastructure is created; this only makes the existing
plumbing actually feed relative motion during a pointer grab.

Signed-off-by: WarChaos Apple Silicon contributors
---
 3 files changed, 16 insertions(+)

diff --git a/dlls/winemac.drv/cocoa_app.m b/dlls/winemac.drv/cocoa_app.m
index 2a9dab2..5967f7c 100644
--- a/dlls/winemac.drv/cocoa_app.m
+++ b/dlls/winemac.drv/cocoa_app.m
@@ -1375,6 +1375,17 @@ static NSString* WineLocalizedString(unsigned int stringID)
                 absolute = TRUE;
                 forceNextMouseMoveAbsolute = FALSE;
             }
+            else if (use_raw_input && clientWantsCursorHidden && self.clippingCursor)
+            {
+                /* FPS pointer grab: always feed relative motion from the CGEvent
+                 * deltas (kCGMouseEventDeltaX/Y, i.e. NSEvent -deltaX/-deltaY) so
+                 * raw input devices registered via RegisterRawInputDevices get
+                 * proper WM_INPUT messages. Mirrors winewayland.drv relative
+                 * pointer behavior (GitLab MR !5869). This avoids the mouselook
+                 * latency caused by the pinned-cursor heuristic below, which only
+                 * emits relative events at clip/desktop boundaries. */
+                absolute = FALSE;
+            }
             else
             {
                 // Send absolute move events if the cursor is in the interior of
diff --git a/dlls/winemac.drv/macdrv_cocoa.h b/dlls/winemac.drv/macdrv_cocoa.h
index 9a91edb..742dc5e 100644
--- a/dlls/winemac.drv/macdrv_cocoa.h
+++ b/dlls/winemac.drv/macdrv_cocoa.h
@@ -124,6 +124,7 @@ extern bool allow_immovable_windows;
 extern bool use_confinement_cursor_clipping;
 extern bool cursor_clipping_locks_windows;
 extern bool use_precise_scrolling;
+extern bool use_raw_input;
 extern int gl_surface_mode;
 extern CFDictionaryRef localized_strings;
 extern bool retina_enabled;  /* Whether Retina mode is enabled via registry setting. */
diff --git a/dlls/winemac.drv/macdrv_main.c b/dlls/winemac.drv/macdrv_main.c
index 9616824..14d57f7 100644
--- a/dlls/winemac.drv/macdrv_main.c
+++ b/dlls/winemac.drv/macdrv_main.c
@@ -53,6 +53,7 @@ BOOL allow_software_rendering = FALSE;
 bool allow_immovable_windows = true;
 bool use_confinement_cursor_clipping = true;
 bool cursor_clipping_locks_windows = true;
+bool use_raw_input = false;
 bool use_precise_scrolling = true;
 int gl_surface_mode = GL_SURFACE_IN_FRONT_OPAQUE;
 bool retina_enabled = false;
@@ -354,6 +355,9 @@ static void setup_options(void)
     if (!get_config_key(hkey, appkey, "CursorClippingLocksWindows", buffer, sizeof(buffer)))
         cursor_clipping_locks_windows = IS_OPTION_TRUE(buffer[0]);
 
+    if (!get_config_key(hkey, appkey, "RawInput", buffer, sizeof(buffer)))
+        use_raw_input = IS_OPTION_TRUE(buffer[0]);
+
     if (!get_config_key(hkey, appkey, "UsePreciseScrolling", buffer, sizeof(buffer)))
         use_precise_scrolling = IS_OPTION_TRUE(buffer[0]);
 
